page (training courses) so

It is one of the most important sections but it is not exhaustive, the
specific contents of the courses are fragmented into several pages.
It includes many categories which could become separated
entries in the menu.
Inconsistency in the nomenclature of the menu subcategories that
do not correspond to the name of the page they open (for instance

Teacher Training 300
The page is exhaustive, it makes clear the
advantages of registering for both company and
employees.
All categories are located in the header.
Input fields are accompanied by a label.
Links, headlines, and keywords have the same color.
The system shows no signs of ongoing activity (yes the platform).
Some content is out of date.

g.text: The CTAs are familiar to the user (e.g. Book, Buy).

text.tspan: Although the website has a mobile version, the desktop interface is
not responsive, so resizing the window doesn't fit the contents.
No breadcrumb or page focus.

g.text: Brand identity is maintained throughout the interface.

text.tspan: Registration / booking forms are not branded.
Forms and
Continuing Training
are entirely in English.
In the mobile version, the registration form is not responsive.
In mobile some texts have an illegible and unreadable font size
(e.g. Calendar).

g.text: All pages are indexed and therefore findable from search engines.
Shortcuts are only available for Buy and Book flows.

g.text: 5. Error prevention
The Shop platform is not fully working(e.g. Products search).
8. Aesthetic and minimalist design

text.tspan: The photos are genuine but don't have high quality.
There is no distinction between interactive and static elements.
Titles, subtitles, keywords, links, buttons have the same color.
Some non-hypertext words / phrases are underlined.
Only for some buttons the hover status is shown.

g.text: The brand color is maintained throughout the interface.
10. Help and documentation

text.tspan: Contacts
in the header is one of the many subcategories in the
About Us therefore is not immediately usable.
No info is provided regarding the accessibility of the website.
There is no FAQ section.
The Regulations in the footer provide all the information
necessary to use the services.
It is possible to contact the company in various ways.
9. Help users recognize, diagnose,
and recover from errors.
No error messages are shown (excluding email form), so a
solution is not suggested.
